   patterns within a discipline using author citation networks. Two metrics
   are designed, including average knowledge flow and average shortest
   distance. They are used to identify the impact and diffusion
   characteristics of inter-specialty knowledge communication. We apply
   these metrics to an empirical data set of Chinese library and
