Abstract = {This article discusses the phenomenon of ``context effects{''} by
   reviewing the findings and practices of a range of scientific fields,
   including astronomy, physics, biology, medicine. and especially the
   relevant research and theory from psychology. Context information, such
   as expectations about what one is supposed to see or conclude, has been
   found to have a small but relentless impact on human perception,
   judgment, and decision-making. The article then considers the
