Abstract = {The influence of authors is mostly based on their capacity to form
   specific self-contained and/or active research communities or topics
   while also inspiring fruitful spin-off research derived from those
   communities or topics. Accurately estimating author influence and its
   indirect effect in inspiring external research creativity must thus be
   based on very precise community roles as well as topic-role analysis on
   citing material. In this paper we thus implement, compare, and combine
   two different kinds of knowledge mapping approaches used to track
   authors' influence over time-a recent topic-based mapping approach and
   an original hybrid community-based mapping approach. The experimental
   context of our study is the analysis of the dynamics and of the
   influence of the research of Prof. Liu Zeyuan, the most important
   contributor in the field of Science of Science in China. This analysis
   focuses on papers citing Professor Liu Zeyuan's research and highlights
   the full extent of his creative thinking.},
