Pages = {90-101},
Month = {APR},
Abstract = {In this paper, I draw on philosophy of science to address a challenge
   for science communication. Empirical research indicates that some people
   who trust a meteorologists report that they are in the path of a storm
   do not trust a climate scientists report that we are on a path to global
   warming. Such selective skepticism about climate science exemplifies a
   more general challenge:
   The Challenge of Selective Uptake
   Laypersons who generally accept public scientific testimony nevertheless
   fail to accept public scientific testimony concerning select, equally
